                <r3d:description language="eng">With more than 60 years of experience, Toronto and Region Conservation Authority (TRCA) is one of 36 Conservation Authorities in Ontario, created to safeguard and enhance the health and well-being of watershed communities through the protection and restoration of the natural environment and the ecological services the environment provides.
At TRCA, we are working towards providing free and open access to our data and information, in both accessible and machine readable formats, to ensure it’s available and easy to consume. Improving access to TRCA’s data and information will provide transparency into the decision making process and will improve accountability while increasing the public’s understanding and engagement with the organization.</r3d:description>
